1

I started the year well ahead of the University Press. Every chapter was overhauled and brought down to date during 1954 so that no more major changes are necessary. Probably the biggest job ahead is to go through chapters 11-13 looking for changes required by reason of new material picked up at the Venom symposium just concluded at Berkley.

Spent the day catching up on all kinds of miscellaneous work.

Page Edit History:
  • pamg 11/24/2012 04:10 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:46 PM

2

Made headway today on the material picked up in Berkeley.

Page Edit History:
  • pamg 11/24/2012 04:11 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:46 PM

3

At the office all morning.

Still on miscellaneous cleanup work in the afternoon and evening.

Page Edit History:
  • pamg 11/24/2012 04:11 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:46 PM

4

At the office in the morning.

Got quite a lot of work done in the afternoon, particularly writing necessary letters.

Price called this afternoon about granting V-P Dolan stock option for 4400 shares effective today. Gave my ok by phone.

Page Edit History:
  • pamg 11/24/2012 04:13 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:46 PM

5

At the office all morning. Tpok lunch with Jack Bailey and Mike Gonsalez to discuss the S.D. Scientific library.

Spent part of the time in the afternoon at the medical library. Got some important new items.

15

Today I completely reread chapter 11 and made final corrections. Also made changes in the carbon copy as a record in reserve.

Went to Scholia tonight.

Today I received the first bunch of galley proofs; these not for corrections, but for a last look at the typography, before too much has been run. Looks OK to me. The foot-note numbers are smaller than I had expected.

32

At the office from 8:30 to 9:30. Met with Richard Blackwelder and Waldo Schmitt from 11 AM until 3:30 to discuss the affairs of the Society of Systematic Zoology of which I am now president. Carl Hubbs joined us at lunch.

Back at the office in the late afternoon.

Notes:

pamg

Date: February 1, 1955

85

Started from Berkeley with G.G. at 9:30 AM on a clear, cool day. Went via US 395 to Cajon Pass, Palmdale, Lancaster, and Gorman, and then U.S. 99. Arrived at Madera at 5:30 P.M. and Merced at 6:30. Put up at the Murrieta Motel. Miles today 431. One dead snake passed up in S.D. Co. - the only lone seen on the entire trip.

Page Edit History:
  • pamg 12/01/2012 04:29 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:46 PM

  • pamg 12/01/2012 04:32 PM

230

At the office in the morning.

Went to Kona Kai with Detty June, Ed, and the kids for lunch. Also A.J..

Some work on indexing Chap 11.

Today I heard from Dr. Bennett of San Rafael who had the recent snake bite case. The victim Lynn Larke, 4 years old, was playing in her back yard when she was bitten by a 3-1/2 foot rattler. 11-10 cc doses of antivenin were administered. She was bitten in the top of the foot. Had severe hemorrhagic symptoms and two onsets of neurotoxic symptoms. The second almost proved fatal. Cortisone was used. The child was hospitalized fo 16 days. Recovery was complete.
